{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01JWvBAuUxZuy2jrQ4xgjwYF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is healthy. Here's what was wrong and what I did:\n\n**Root cause:** `app-user` had write and read permissions on the `/app` vhost but an empty **configure** permission. In RabbitMQ, `configure` permission is required to declare (create) queues and exchanges. Without it, the producer got `Access refused` when calling `queue.declare`.\n\n**Fix:** Granted `app-user` full configure/write/read on `/app`:\n```\nrabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /app app-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"\n```\n\n**Verified state:**\n- `app-producer` is `1/1 Running` (no restarts after the fix)\n- `/app` vhost contains `app-queue` of type `classic` with messages (7 messages accumulated)\n- All 3 RabbitMQ nodes (`rabbitmq-0/1/2`) remain `Running`"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":385,"cache_read_input_tokens":30931,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":385},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"150244a9-ad00-47d1-8506-7eae6252d778","uuid":"3c6e75aa-f705-4c57-9b16-42174ede0a0c","request_id":"req_011CccTNYKs9iKeV69h7ZXKe"}
